verbose_text: A study consisted of 11 blood samples from iMCD patients during flare-up showed low IL-6 level, and pro inflammatory cytokine like interferon-gamma-induced protein 10 (IP-10) and tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha were found elevated.13, 14 Since our patient has HHV-8 negative iMCD with TAFRO syndrome, IP-10, and TNF-alpha could have been the potent prognostic and diagnostic markers for her therapy response instead of relying on VEGF level alone.
